profile_positions.description:
- Management of mixed portfolio of corporate clients;
- Advising on the tax efficient acquisition structures (share deal vs. asset deal) and post-acquisition integration within the group; 
- Advising on the set-up of the fund structure (Mauritius and the UAE);
- Advising multinational corporations looking to establish operations in the Middle East and also with Middle East based groups looking to expand overseas;
- Detailed BEPS assessment of the holding, financing and IP structures for various multinational groups across different sectors including: banking, technology, telecommunication, education, private wealth management, oil & gas, hospitality and leisure;
- Post-BEPS tax advisory, including - interest deductibility, anti-avoidance and double tax treaty analysis with the view of MLI implications;
- Advice on withholding tax and permanent establishment considerations with respect to the cross-border operations;
- Assisting with developing and evaluating European planning opportunities in light of the direct tax developments (e.g. ATAD I & II);
- Leading the implementation of tax planning strategies and worldwide restructurings;
- Co-ordination with other offices and external advisors in a multi-office engagement and reviews inputs received from such offices / advisors.
- Overseeing local tax compliance (direct and indirect tax reporting obligations and CbCR, local file and master file), including analysis and interpretation of the financial and commercial data;
- Reviewing tax research for tax planning and compliance reporting;
- Monitoring worldwide taxation developments and initiative (BEPS, Brexit, ATAD etc.);
- Lead, mentor, and develop the international section of the International tax team; and
- Tax Performance Advisory (TPA) projects involving preparation and implementation of tax strategies and tax policies to the clients in the region.

Tax Assistant Manager in International Tax Department:
- Managing the successful delivery of international tax projects, ensuring technical excellence and provide practical solutions. This includes advising international groups on a range of cross border tax issues, group structuring, tax efficient financing, inbound and outbound investment;
- Identifying tax planning opportunities;
- Managing cross border teams and client service teams on an ongoing basis on advisory  projects. This involves liaising with specialists, overseas member firms and external advisers to deliver successful projects and expertise; 
- Assist Directors and Partners with specific (International) advisory projects including in respect of BEPS (Base Erosion & Profit Shifting), permanent establishments and withholding tax.
- Taxation of foreign branches ;
- Building and maintaining relationships with clients and providing high levels of client service.
- Research in relation to ad hoc tax issues; 
- Coaching and developing junior members of staff; and
- Assisting with business development work.

Tax Assistant Manager in International Tax Department:
- Management of mixed portfolio of corporate clients;
- Advise foreign multinational companies on the tax implications of their operations, providing  practical advice in relation to uncertain tax positions;
- Corresponding with both Revenue and clients on the clients' tax affairs;
- Managing corporate tax compliance;
- Researching and presenting detailed technical tax memorandums to support tax advisory projects;
- Working as part of a team with fellow managers, directors and partners, ensuring the smooth running of the department;
- Involvement in sustaining and growth of client business, proposing and winning new business and positively contributing to the overall development of the practice;
- Aligning operational model requirements with tax planning, to achieve sustainable client benefits;
- Supervision and development of a Junior staff;
- Co-ordination with other offices in a multi-office engagement and reviews inputs received from such offices;
- Reviewing client base to identify tax planning opportunities; and
- Various ad hoc duties and responsibilities as directed by management.

Tax Senior in International Tax Department:
- Assisting in the management of a mixed portfolio of clients; 
- Advise foreign multinational companies on the tax implications of their operations, providing practical advice in relation to uncertain tax positions;
- Co-ordinates with other offices in a multi-office engagement, and reviews inputs received from such offices;
- Managing the compliance requirements of a broad portfolio of clients;
- Interpreting legislation and identifying precedent in preparing tax returns;
- Researching EU and other international tax related developments;
- Liaising with other departments to plan and provide professional tax advice; 
- Identifying tax planning opportunities;
- Due diligence;
- Research in relation to client taxation issues; and
- Various ad hoc duties and responsibilities as directed by management.
